<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7287> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7287" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 39, listed in the SC de Aphrodisiensibus. According to J. M. Reynolds (Aphrodisias and Rome, 72) the kappa of the nomen ]# is clear, although cognomen and tribe (Fab.) are consistent with the name of T. Atinius Tyrannus in the SC de Panamareis (Sherk, RDGE 158, no. 27). Cf. MRR 2.488. Badian, in comments on the names in the SC (ZPE 55, 1984, 111-112) is also inclined to favor the name T. Atinius Tyrannus.\n" .
